00:45:11,279 --> 00:45:13,248
We're a little noisy.

464
00:45:21,956 --> 00:45:24,158
Hi, George, it's Jane--

465
00:45:28,530 --> 00:45:32,500
I sensed things were off
when he got back from L.A...

466
00:45:32,767 --> 00:45:38,039
...but I thought he was tired.
Then he says France isn't a good idea.

467
00:45:38,273 --> 00:45:42,277
He'll have to work the whole time.
Still, no big deal.

468
00:45:42,544 --> 00:45:47,081
So he gets on a plane and goes alone.
Right? Wrong.

469
00:45:47,382 --> 00:45:50,652
An hour ago, I call to say good night.

470
00:45:50,852 --> 00:45:54,155
Guess who answered,
1:00 a.m., Paris time?

471
00:45:54,522 --> 00:45:58,293
-Penelope Pope.
-Who's Penelope Pope?

472
00:45:58,526 --> 00:46:01,963
She's the answer to:
"Who the fuck is this?!"

473
00:46:02,163 --> 00:46:06,067
-Oh, God, Liz, I'm sorry.
-I don't get it!

474
00:46:06,301 --> 00:46:11,539
Why feed me all that romantic crap
if he's just gonna cheat?

475
00:46:11,739 --> 00:46:14,909
-Two words: copulatory imperative.
-What?

476
00:46:15,410 --> 00:46:18,246
The biological urge to spread seed.

477
00:46:19,581 --> 00:46:22,050
Less than 5% of male animals
are monogamous.

478
00:46:22,317 --> 00:46:26,988
-The other 95% are....
-Plugging Penelope Pope.

479
00:46:38,900 --> 00:46:42,704
I stopped by H and H
and picked up...

480
00:46:42,904 --> 00:46:48,676
...a sesame seed bagel,
lightly toasted, just like you liked.

481
00:47:04,259 --> 00:47:10,932
I hope Ray's cold turns into pneumonia
and bed rest causes abs to atrophy.

482
00:47:15,970 --> 00:47:21,276
Ben wants a women's column. It hit
him, 20% of our readers are female.

483
00:47:21,476 --> 00:47:24,012
The idea is for it to be about men.

484
00:47:24,245 --> 00:47:28,183
How they're paranoid
about going bald and what not.

485
00:47:28,416 --> 00:47:30,185
-So?
-Forget baldness.

486
00:47:30,385 --> 00:47:34,489
The real issue is their behavior,
their copulatory impulse.

487
00:47:34,756 --> 00:47:40,395
-Imperative. More hot water, please.
-I think you should write it.

488
00:47:40,628 --> 00:47:43,097
-Are you crazy?
-Well, why not?

489
00:47:43,298 --> 00:47:48,636
-I'm not a writer or a psychologist.
-So? We need someone with experience.

490
00:47:48,837 --> 00:47:52,073
Liz, I don't know what
I'm talking about.

491
00:47:52,273 --> 00:47:55,977
I just have notebooks
filled with ridiculous facts.

492
00:47:56,177 --> 00:48:02,317
This is not a full-time job.
It's a sick, twisted, pathetic hobby.

493
00:48:02,584 --> 00:48:05,920
So get paid to write
about your obsession.

494
00:48:06,120 --> 00:48:09,023
If you want,
we'll give you a pen name.

495
00:48:09,257 --> 00:48:16,130
It'd be cathartic for you. Do your
dear, sweet friend a huge favor.

496
00:48:18,867 --> 00:48:20,602
Pen name, huh?

497
00:48:26,708 --> 00:48:30,745
-I'm doing this once. One time.
-Fine. It'll be fun.

498
00:48:30,979 --> 00:48:35,383
I'm concocting the background
of a nonexistent scientist...

499
00:48:35,617 --> 00:48:40,355
...about to publish her delusional
theories in a men's magazine.

500
00:48:40,555 --> 00:48:43,024
You're right. This is fun.

501
00:48:43,525 --> 00:48:49,797
Okay, try this. Born in Sussex, 1937.

502
00:48:51,132 --> 00:48:57,405
Cofounder of the Institute of
Pathological Narcissism in Vienna.

503
00:49:09,817 --> 00:49:11,052
Who is she?

504
00:49:11,252 --> 00:49:15,557
The recently deceased Harriet Gould.
No surviving relatives.

505
00:49:15,757 --> 00:49:19,794
-She's perfect. She even has a bun.
-That's her.

506
00:49:20,562 --> 00:49:25,433
Dr. Marie Charles. Oh, my God.

507
00:49:58,933 --> 00:50:04,072
Every bull begins a relationship
with aces up his sleeve.

508
00:50:04,305 --> 00:50:08,643
Tools of seduction
by which he lures a New Cow.

509
00:50:08,910 --> 00:50:13,648
One of the most notorious examples
is the Current Cow Sob Story.

510
00:50:13,882 --> 00:50:17,385
Allow me to deconstruct
the essential elements:

511
00:50:17,619 --> 00:50:22,891
You're so easy to talk to.
Not like my Current Cow.

512
00:50:23,091 --> 00:50:25,460
The Myth of Male Shyness:

513
00:50:25,660 --> 00:50:29,597
You think he's flattering you?
He's flattering himself.

514
00:50:29,797 --> 00:50:33,001
Showing how sensitive
and honest he is.

515
00:50:35,470 --> 00:50:43,244
I just try so hard. I'm sure she
doesn't mean to be a Cold Cow.

516
00:50:43,444 --> 00:50:46,748
In case you think he's
a cold-hearted womanizer...

517
00:50:46,948 --> 00:50:51,286
...he'll say this to show he's
leaving his Cow for a reason...

518
00:50:51,519 --> 00:50:54,956
...and he's tormented
by the thought of leaving her.

519
00:50:55,156 --> 00:50:58,526
What do they say about
the love of a good woman?

520
00:50:58,760 --> 00:51:03,264
That, once offered, it'll
come back and bite her in the ass.

521
00:51:03,498 --> 00:51:05,133
Enter: case in point.

522
00:51:05,333 --> 00:51:09,771
-You're not with what's-her-name?
-Didn't work out.

523
00:51:10,004 --> 00:51:15,944
Get a little saddle sore on your
white horse? So, what happened?

524
00:51:16,177 --> 00:51:22,050
-Lost interest.
-What do you mean? How exactly?

525
00:51:22,684 --> 00:51:26,120
Do we really have to have
another postmortem?

526
00:51:26,354 --> 00:51:32,360
I'm just curious is all. So you went
to a movie? Then back to her place?

527
00:51:33,328 --> 00:51:34,696
Then what?

528
00:51:35,697 --> 00:51:39,367
We're in the kitchen,
and she's looking for food.

529
00:51:39,567 --> 00:51:43,738
We'd had dinner after the movie,
but she's still hungry.

530
00:51:43,972 --> 00:51:49,744
-She's always hungry, it seems.
-And that's bad? Women who eat?

531
00:51:53,348 --> 00:51:59,320
You're in the kitchen, she's hungry
again, inexplicably. Then what?

532
00:51:59,854 --> 00:52:02,991
So she takes out
a pint of Häagen-Dazs...

533
00:52:03,491 --> 00:52:07,896
...then starts eating it, standing
there, out of the container.

534
00:52:08,096 --> 00:52:12,901
-Something about it turned me off.
-Was the refrigerator door open?

535
00:52:13,101 --> 00:52:15,837
-Why?
-Answer the question.

536
00:52:16,037 --> 00:52:20,375
-It was open, I think.
-Would it matter if it were shut?

537
00:52:20,575 --> 00:52:25,380
Would that have made a nonfat woman
eating ice cream less revolting?

538
00:52:25,580 --> 00:52:31,519
What if she were hungry before shoving
her face into a trough of Häagen-Dazs?

539
00:52:31,753 --> 00:52:34,122
Is using a dish less repulsive?

540
00:52:34,355 --> 00:52:38,526
-Good night, you psycho!
-Good night, you neophiliac!

541
00:52:43,464 --> 00:52:48,036
You sitting down?
Oprah read the article on her show.

542
00:52:48,303 --> 00:52:53,141
The audience loved it. She's begging
for Dr. Charles to be a guest!

543
00:52:53,374 --> 00:52:55,877
Everyone in PR has a different story.

544
00:52:56,110 --> 00:52:59,380
She's in Hong Kong,
she's in Tangiers....

545
00:52:59,614 --> 00:53:02,684
-This is bad.
-No, this is all good.

546
00:53:02,951 --> 00:53:07,922
Trust me. I've got it under control.
This won't come anywhere near you.

547
00:53:08,156 --> 00:53:10,625
"While the male may seem shy...

548
00:53:10,959 --> 00:53:15,730
...with his Uriah Heep hand-wringing
and 'Aw, shucks' toe-kicking...

549
00:53:15,930 --> 00:53:20,902
...he is actually a narcissist
because this apparent shyness...

550
00:53:21,135 --> 00:53:24,072
...belies the more
deeply rooted feelings...

551
00:53:24,272 --> 00:53:27,942
...of unworthiness
and fear of rejection.

552
00:53:28,142 --> 00:53:32,347
And this is what compels him
to constantly seek attention...

553
00:53:32,614 --> 00:53:38,119
...from New Cow after New Cow,
ad nauseam, ad infinitum."

554
00:53:38,419 --> 00:53:40,488
This is such great stuff.

555
00:53:40,755 --> 00:53:45,994
It destroys any sentimentality we have
about what noble creatures men are.

556
00:53:46,194 --> 00:53:50,532
Here's what we're looking for.
It's provocative, it's clever.

557
00:53:50,765 --> 00:53:52,800
It's got mass appeal.

558
00:53:53,034 --> 00:53:58,072
But nobody can find this woman.
The Today Show's tried, Oprah's tried.

559
00:53:58,506 --> 00:54:01,142
-And have you tried?
-Eddie?

560
00:54:01,376 --> 00:54:06,915
-Well, no.
-Do you know what we're talking about?

561
00:54:08,149 --> 00:54:12,587
-The "ungettable get."
-Yes! I don't care what it takes.

562
00:54:12,854 --> 00:54:17,992
You find that Dr. Marie Charles
and bring her to my studio.

563
00:54:18,193 --> 00:54:22,864
Your friend works at M, and she has
no idea where the doctor is?

564
00:54:23,131 --> 00:54:25,834
-That's what she said.
-I don't buy that.

565
00:54:26,034 --> 00:54:28,903
-Why are you holding out on me?
-I'm not.

566
00:54:29,204 --> 00:54:31,172
-Give me her number.
-No.

567
00:54:31,406 --> 00:54:35,310
Besides, you'd never reach her.
She's at Jivamukti.

568
00:54:35,510 --> 00:54:37,212
-Yoga.
-Yoga what?

569
00:54:37,478 --> 00:54:39,447
Jivamukti.

570
00:54:42,851 --> 00:54:45,820
-Manhattan. Jivamukti.
-Eddie!

571
00:54:46,087 --> 00:54:51,159
-It's a yoga place.
-Eddie, don't be a jerk.

572
00:54:55,563 --> 00:54:59,767
Eddie, come on, this is so ridiculous.

573
00:55:00,001 --> 00:55:03,438
You have to leave your shoes in here.

574
00:55:06,574 --> 00:55:09,444
Liz? Excuse me, is--?

575
00:55:11,012 --> 00:55:15,917
Jerk, she's my best friend.
I'd know if there's anything going--

576
00:55:17,752 --> 00:55:19,320
Stay!

577
00:55:19,787 --> 00:55:23,024
Bring your leg up.
Sir, you have to leave.

578
00:55:23,224 --> 00:55:27,195
Sorry. I'm just looking
for a friend. Oh, God!

579
00:55:29,364 --> 00:55:31,533
-You okay?
-Eddie.

580
00:55:35,236 --> 00:55:37,238
How you doing, Becca?

581
00:55:38,573 --> 00:55:39,941
I'm good.

582
00:55:42,477 --> 00:55:44,579
What are you doing here?

583
00:55:49,250 --> 00:55:50,785
I don't know.

584
00:55:51,319 --> 00:55:55,356
Forget about this disturbance.
It's okay.

585
00:55:55,590 --> 00:55:59,527
Get back to your spaces
and prepare for lion pose.

586
00:55:59,894 --> 00:56:04,365
Inhale, exhale, open your mouths,
stick out your tongue.

587
00:56:04,632 --> 00:56:08,069
That was Rebecca?
Eddie, talk to me.

588
00:56:08,303 --> 00:56:11,639
There's nothing to talk about.
Hi, Liz.

589
00:56:11,840 --> 00:56:13,808
You cannot believe.

590
00:56:14,509 --> 00:56:16,578
-Janie!
-Hi, guys.

591
00:56:16,845 --> 00:56:19,914
Eddie, this is Alice and Stephen.

592
00:56:20,148 --> 00:56:22,917
-You're Eddie?
-Yeah.

593
00:56:23,918 --> 00:56:28,623
-Are you taking yoga together?
-We were-- It's stupid.

594
00:56:28,823 --> 00:56:33,261
-We don't think it's stupid.
-We started a pregnancy class.

595
00:56:33,494 --> 00:56:36,197
-Congratulations.
-She's a great breather.

596
00:56:36,431 --> 00:56:40,602
-Listen, I gotta go.
-It was really nice to meet you.

597
00:57:19,407 --> 00:57:22,610
Eddie preferred
to leave things unsaid...

598
00:57:22,810 --> 00:57:26,781
...and went back to grazing
in greener pastures.

599
00:57:31,653 --> 00:57:35,323
Merry Christmas, everyone.
Merry Christmas.

600
00:57:35,557 --> 00:57:38,560
-I'll be back.
-Okay.

601
00:57:41,229 --> 00:57:43,731
-Two champagnes, please.
-Yes, sir.

602
00:57:43,998 --> 00:57:48,269
Shouldn't that be a champagne
and a Shirley Temple? Sorry.

603
00:57:48,503 --> 00:57:52,373
-No, you're not.
-So where'd you meet her?

604
00:57:52,607 --> 00:57:58,413
-She's Emily's roommate.
-I made coffee for Emily last Sunday.

605
00:58:00,515 --> 00:58:06,020
-Isn't that complicated?
-It's never complicated, Jane.

606
00:58:06,354 --> 00:58:09,557
-Thank you.
-Blintzes, not Blitzen.

607
00:58:25,306 --> 00:58:29,711
-Good evening. What can I get you?
-Scotch, please.

608
00:58:31,279 --> 00:58:34,082
Hear Diane's joke
about the reindeer?

609
00:58:35,550 --> 00:58:37,485
Funny!

610
00:58:42,056 --> 00:58:44,092
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

611
00:58:53,234 --> 00:58:55,136
I miss you, Jane.

612
00:59:02,644 --> 00:59:05,813
Am I supposed to walk away now?

613
00:59:13,421 --> 00:59:16,858
Can we get away from this?
Can we do something?

614
00:59:17,091 --> 00:59:20,828
Get together for lunch, dinner.
Friday night?

615
00:59:22,697 --> 00:59:28,703
-Friday is New Year's Eve.
-Oh. That's right. That's right.

616
00:59:28,937 --> 00:59:31,873
-You probably have plans.
-Don't you?

617
00:59:32,140 --> 00:59:36,044
Yeah. Yes, I do.
Yes, I do. I--

618
00:59:44,118 --> 00:59:45,954
I have none.

619
00:59:47,989 --> 00:59:51,426
Could I call you?
Would that be okay?

620
00:59:59,868 --> 01:00:01,836
Merry Christmas, Jane.

621
01:00:08,376 --> 01:00:13,414
You can't stop now. You're syndicated
in over 300 newspapers.

622
01:00:13,648 --> 01:00:16,050
Talk radio's having a field day.

623
01:00:16,251 --> 01:00:20,688
-The world's one giant Used Cow lot.
-I want to think about it.

624
01:00:20,922 --> 01:00:25,393
Think? You don't want to be
a post feminist icon?

625
01:00:25,660 --> 01:00:29,397
Let's get something great to wear
for Julian's party.

626
01:00:31,165 --> 01:00:35,503
I meant to tell you that
I kind of made other plans.

627
01:00:35,703 --> 01:00:40,375
-It's nothing major--
-What are you talking about?

628
01:00:41,209 --> 01:00:43,945
-Ray asked me out.
-Ray?

629
01:00:45,346 --> 01:00:49,817
As in Ray Brown?
As in devil incarnate?

630
01:00:50,118 --> 01:00:54,255
No! No, I forbid it!
I thought you were over this.

631
01:00:54,722 --> 01:00:57,192
I'm having second thoughts.

632
01:00:57,725 --> 01:01:02,330
Oh, so now Dr. Charles
is having them too.

633
01:01:12,907 --> 01:01:15,777
-Done yet?
-You got a hot date?

634
01:01:15,977 --> 01:01:18,880
-No, I just have to pee.
-Be my guest.

635
01:01:19,080 --> 01:01:23,484
-What's this? Party Viagra?
-No. It's nicotine gum.

636
01:01:23,718 --> 01:01:27,689
-When did you quit?
-Daphne wants to marry a smoker.

637
01:01:27,922 --> 01:01:29,290
Here.

638
01:01:30,491 --> 01:01:31,793
Thank you.

639
01:01:32,627 --> 01:01:36,598
-Come out with me tonight.
-To trail after your harem?

640
01:01:36,931 --> 01:01:40,301
I'm flying solo
to keep my options open.

641
01:01:41,236 --> 01:01:43,438
Although that may be for me.

642
01:01:46,307 --> 01:01:48,910
-Hello.
-Have you come to your senses?

643
01:01:49,143 --> 01:01:51,946
No. Quit worrying about me.

644
01:01:52,146 --> 01:01:55,950
Have a good time.
I'll wear the lipstick you gave me.

645
01:01:56,150 --> 01:01:57,952
-Okay, bye.
-Bye.

646
01:02:04,626 --> 01:02:06,861
Why are you doing this?

647
01:02:08,329 --> 01:02:09,597
Doing what?

648
01:02:10,465 --> 01:02:14,202
-Ray.
-What are you talking about?

649
01:02:17,939 --> 01:02:20,642
If you change your mind,
I'll be here.

650
01:02:20,842 --> 01:02:25,013
Thanks. I think I'll just
jump into my P.J.s...

651
01:02:25,213 --> 01:02:29,150
...probably watch a little TV,
go to bed early.

652
01:02:29,350 --> 01:02:31,786
-Happy New Year.
-Same to you.

653
01:02:52,507 --> 01:02:57,145
Back to our special New Year's Eve
coverage with Hugh Downs.

654
01:02:57,345 --> 01:03:00,849
It was less than 48 hours ago
that Ray Brown called...

655
01:03:01,082 --> 01:03:04,452
...to confirm plans
with Jane Goodale tonight...

656
01:03:04,652 --> 01:03:09,657
...a clear indication he regretted
terminating their involvement.

657
01:03:09,891 --> 01:03:13,828
So the question remains:
Why hasn't he shown up yet?

658
01:03:14,062 --> 01:03:19,767
It appears that Mr. Brown is sticking
firmly to his September sanctions.

659
01:04:21,129 --> 01:04:26,067
Ten, nine, eight, seven...

660
01:04:26,301 --> 01:04:31,940
...six, five, four, three, two, one!

661
01:04:32,140 --> 01:04:33,842
Happy New Year!

662
01:05:14,115 --> 01:05:15,350
Jane!

663
01:05:38,473 --> 01:05:40,141
Sorry.

664
01:05:40,542 --> 01:05:42,810
-Jane?
-Don't even bother.

665
01:05:43,845 --> 01:05:46,014
I need to talk to you.

666
01:05:47,315 --> 01:05:52,253
-Why didn't you return my calls?
-After the one you didn't make?

667
01:05:52,520 --> 01:05:55,356
-It's not true.
-It's so true.

668
01:06:02,063 --> 01:06:04,132
Stop for a moment.

669
01:06:05,400 --> 01:06:08,403
-I know it's inexcusable.
-Good morning.

670
01:06:08,670 --> 01:06:11,706
-There's a reason I didn't go.
-I'm sure.

671
01:06:12,006 --> 01:06:17,879
-I don't care, so forget about it.
-Will you hear me out?

672
01:06:18,112 --> 01:06:21,449
You know what, Ray?
The truth is-- Hi.

673
01:06:21,950 --> 01:06:26,754
You did me a favor.
Any delusions I had are gone now.

674
01:06:26,955 --> 01:06:31,860
