time in months, I feel great.

675
01:06:32,460 --> 01:06:35,997
-Staff meeting in two minutes.
-Be right there.

676
01:06:39,234 --> 01:06:40,969
What's wrong?

677
01:06:43,137 --> 01:06:45,206
Diane's wearing your shirt.

678
01:06:46,241 --> 01:06:49,110
The one I bought you
on the sidewalk.

679
01:06:54,649 --> 01:07:00,922
-So, are the two of you...?
-We're seeing each other again, yes.

680
01:07:01,422 --> 01:07:04,125
-I'm trying to explain.
-Wait. Stop.

681
01:07:05,059 --> 01:07:08,062
Did you say "again"?

682
01:07:08,663 --> 01:07:12,800
I should've told you, but Diane
insisted on keeping it quiet.

683
01:07:13,001 --> 01:07:16,337
We got back together
and went away for a while.

684
01:07:16,604 --> 01:07:19,007
It's terrible that I didn't call--

685
01:07:19,274 --> 01:07:22,110
Ray, I got Tony Robbins
on line three.

686
01:07:23,144 --> 01:07:26,147
-Go on.
-I'm really sorry, Jane.

687
01:07:47,101 --> 01:07:49,170
Hey, what is it?

688
01:07:49,938 --> 01:07:52,774
-She's Dee.
-I'm not following.

689
01:07:53,041 --> 01:07:58,379
-Diane is Dee.
-Yes, "D" is for Diane, "E" for Eddie.

690
01:07:58,680 --> 01:08:03,184
Ray's Dee. She's the one.
I mean, she was the one, she is....

691
01:08:03,885 --> 01:08:07,856
Whoa, whoa. Just breathe.
Breathe, Jane.

692
01:08:08,122 --> 01:08:11,693
-Ray and Diane are together?
-Back together, again.

693
01:08:12,026 --> 01:08:14,896
I get it. Let it go.
Ray and Diane?

694
01:08:15,196 --> 01:08:17,632
-Yeah!
-Okay, it doesn't matter.

695
01:08:17,866 --> 01:08:21,703
That chapter's over.
We gotta go, so pull it together.

696
01:08:21,970 --> 01:08:24,405
Do you hear me?
Don't cry.

697
01:08:24,806 --> 01:08:27,275
-Please. You'll be fine.
-Okay.

698
01:08:27,542 --> 01:08:29,978
-We're going in. Good.
-Okay.

699
01:08:30,211 --> 01:08:32,013
You all right?

700
01:08:34,048 --> 01:08:37,018
Jane, where are we for next week?

701
01:08:37,719 --> 01:08:41,022
We're set with Gérard Depardieu.
Right, Jane?

702
01:08:41,322 --> 01:08:44,559
Oh, good. New movie?

703
01:08:45,059 --> 01:08:48,930
Amazing. I actually....
I saw it.

704
01:08:49,163 --> 01:08:54,669
It's about a man whose marriage
falls apart. It's brutal.

705
01:08:54,936 --> 01:09:00,742
You see the love story first.
This woman means everything to him.

706
01:09:01,009 --> 01:09:07,282
In fact, there's this scene where he
actually sits in just a dark--

707
01:09:08,116 --> 01:09:11,753
It's very touching.
He sits in a dark room and just--

708
01:09:12,120 --> 01:09:17,392
You just start to see the tears
and stuff. The man is completely...

709
01:09:17,625 --> 01:09:22,030
...broken and you really feel it.
It's devastating.

710
01:09:24,732 --> 01:09:26,401
Is this a joke?

711
01:09:29,070 --> 01:09:30,738
No, what do you mean?

712
01:09:33,641 --> 01:09:36,811
I mean, is this a joke?

713
01:09:37,979 --> 01:09:40,448
No, I saw it two nights ago.

714
01:09:41,049 --> 01:09:45,753
-What's so funny, Jane?
-Can you believe this guy?

715
01:09:45,987 --> 01:09:47,956
So sensitive...

716
01:09:48,156 --> 01:09:52,060
...so devastated over
some chubby French guy.

717
01:09:52,293 --> 01:09:55,096
But stomp on somebody's real heart...

718
01:09:55,396 --> 01:09:57,899
...and where's his pity then?
Nowhere.

719
01:09:58,266 --> 01:10:00,001
Why? He doesn't get it!

720
01:10:00,735 --> 01:10:04,572
He never gets it!
Someone explain it to me.

721
01:10:04,939 --> 01:10:08,776
Because I don't know what
you are talking about!

722
01:10:17,252 --> 01:10:18,753
Evelyn, is she free?

723
01:10:18,987 --> 01:10:22,257
-Yeah, she is.
-Thanks.

724
01:10:31,432 --> 01:10:35,103
I'm sorry, Diane.
I don't know where that came from.

725
01:10:35,703 --> 01:10:38,606
I know exactly
where it came from.

726
01:10:39,641 --> 01:10:43,144
-You do?
-Some guy crushed you...

727
01:10:43,444 --> 01:10:48,950
...and you lashed out at poor Ray as
being representative of him.

728
01:10:49,184 --> 01:10:52,487
-I'm right, aren't I?
-More or less.

729
01:10:52,954 --> 01:10:57,425
-Despite the hurt, you can't do it.
-I know.

730
01:10:57,725 --> 01:11:00,795
No, you don't know.
Sit and listen to me.

731
01:11:05,200 --> 01:11:07,902
I'm gonna let you
in on a secret.

732
01:11:09,571 --> 01:11:14,375
About six months ago,
my boyfriend tried to leave me.

733
01:11:15,043 --> 01:11:21,316
Well, he did, he left.
I was devastated. I was destroyed.

734
01:11:21,716 --> 01:11:23,351
Did you see it?

735
01:11:25,587 --> 01:11:29,490
-No, I didn't.
-Right.

736
01:11:29,724 --> 01:11:35,997
Know why? Because if I fall apart,
everything around me falls apart.

737
01:11:36,564 --> 01:11:41,069
Everything that I have worked
my entire life for.

738
01:11:41,402 --> 01:11:44,005
-Do you love him?
-Who?

739
01:11:44,239 --> 01:11:45,740
Him. The guy.

740
01:11:47,542 --> 01:11:51,913
-I don't know.
-Yes, you do. Have you talked to him?

741
01:11:53,047 --> 01:11:55,884
Well, no, not exactly talked.

742
01:11:56,551 --> 01:11:59,854
Do it. Do it.
Talk to him.

743
01:12:02,090 --> 01:12:06,961
I used to feel that if I
kept my heart to myself...

744
01:12:07,228 --> 01:12:10,265
...if I never expressed
how much I needed him...

745
01:12:10,565 --> 01:12:14,602
...he would never leave me.
Well, guess what? He did.

746
01:12:14,903 --> 01:12:19,507
And I lived in a private,
pathetic puddle.

747
01:12:19,874 --> 01:12:23,077
Until I couldn't stand it.
You know what I did?

748
01:12:23,311 --> 01:12:29,484
I went to him with two corned beef
sandwiches on rye, lightly toasted.

749
01:12:30,385 --> 01:12:33,721
And I told him that
I was lost without him.

750
01:12:34,422 --> 01:12:36,524
You said that?

751
01:12:37,091 --> 01:12:39,894
Pretty progressive, huh?
And I'm happy.

752
01:12:40,128 --> 01:12:41,996
Never thought I'd be happy.

753
01:12:47,669 --> 01:12:52,507
And you believe her? This is love?
What we should all be looking for?

754
01:12:52,740 --> 01:12:55,210
That is so tragic.

755
01:12:55,510 --> 01:12:59,981
Her boyfriend was screwing you
in order to get away from her...

756
01:13:00,315 --> 01:13:05,320
...and she's the authority on romance?
She has to believe that crap.

757
01:13:05,620 --> 01:13:07,155
She's an Old Cow.

758
01:13:08,356 --> 01:13:11,326
All we need to do is
adjust our radar a bit.

759
01:13:11,593 --> 01:13:14,996
Learn to be attracted to
men who don't attract us.

760
01:13:15,196 --> 01:13:18,032
Hang on.
What are you talking about?

761
01:13:18,366 --> 01:13:20,935
Well, for example, normally...

762
01:13:21,703 --> 01:13:25,540
...I'd be attracted to you.
But thanks to Dr. Charles...

763
01:13:25,773 --> 01:13:30,445
...I've learned to control
my passion for testosterone.

764
01:13:30,678 --> 01:13:34,949
And now I'm proud to say
I don't find you attractive at all.

765
01:13:35,216 --> 01:13:37,018
Well, gee, that's swell.

766
01:13:38,553 --> 01:13:40,388
I need a drink.

767
01:13:42,390 --> 01:13:46,661
-Does she know she's insane?
-No, she's right.

768
01:13:46,961 --> 01:13:51,833
-Ray cannot go back to an Old Cow.
-Okay, that's it.

769
01:13:52,300 --> 01:13:56,638
Jane, these are people, not cows.

770
01:14:08,483 --> 01:14:09,984
Hello?

771
01:14:16,891 --> 01:14:20,461
-I knew you'd take his side.
-This isn't about sides.

772
01:14:20,728 --> 01:14:23,665
It's about reality.
You need to get a grip.

773
01:14:23,898 --> 01:14:28,736
That's rich, coming from an emotional
moron whoring through Manhattan...

774
01:14:29,003 --> 01:14:32,340
-...using women like ATM machines.
-Great.

775
01:14:32,574 --> 01:14:34,909
So I'm a moron for sleeping around.

776
01:14:35,176 --> 01:14:40,048
You, you get dumped and become the
disciple of some crone scientist...

777
01:14:40,281 --> 01:14:43,251
...who can't distinguish
humans from animals.

778
01:14:43,451 --> 01:14:47,722
-She is not a crone!
-Who gives a shit?!

779
01:14:48,389 --> 01:14:54,429
While you were buying these theories
about why guys don't come back...

780
01:14:54,729 --> 01:14:56,898
...you were hoping Ray would.

781
01:14:57,198 --> 01:15:00,835
Men are scum, but please, Ray,
make a liar out of me.

782
01:15:01,102 --> 01:15:07,475
Well, you got what you asked for.
He went back, but with the wrong girl.

783
01:15:08,810 --> 01:15:11,412
It's over. Over.

784
01:15:13,147 --> 01:15:14,949
-Why not let go?
-Because.

785
01:15:15,216 --> 01:15:18,052
-Because why?
-Because I can't.

786
01:15:18,319 --> 01:15:21,256
-Why?
-Because I was happy!

787
01:15:21,489 --> 01:15:26,060
Because if the theory is wrong,
men don't leave all women, Eddie...

788
01:15:26,327 --> 01:15:28,663
...they leave me.

789
01:15:35,303 --> 01:15:38,606
I know what it does to you.
I know.

790
01:15:39,073 --> 01:15:42,243
Maybe that's why
we hold on so hard.

791
01:15:43,178 --> 01:15:47,982
We can't believe that such a miracle
can happen twice.

792
01:15:51,853 --> 01:15:53,655
But it can.

793
01:15:56,925 --> 01:16:01,362
Someday you'll find it again.
I promise you.

794
01:16:02,030 --> 01:16:06,768
-Look at me, I'm a mess.
-I'm looking at you.

795
01:16:10,038 --> 01:16:11,973
And you're beautiful.

796
01:16:14,475 --> 01:16:16,778
You are beautiful.

797
01:16:18,880 --> 01:16:20,915
You're intelligent...

798
01:16:21,983 --> 01:16:24,686
...and real.

799
01:16:28,957 --> 01:16:32,727
And Ray's not the last man
you'll ever love.

800
01:16:42,170 --> 01:16:44,672
I promise you he's not.

801
01:18:38,920 --> 01:18:40,455
Listen....

802
01:18:44,125 --> 01:18:45,293
No, no, no.

803
01:18:47,629 --> 01:18:52,100
-You're not gonna analyze this one.
-I'm not?

804
01:18:52,767 --> 01:18:54,402
No, no.

805
01:18:55,470 --> 01:18:59,207
You want things to fit so much
that you miss the fun.

806
01:19:02,877 --> 01:19:08,716
You're rationalizing last night.
Worried about what might've happened.

807
01:19:08,983 --> 01:19:13,621
I get a kick out of spending
an entire night with you in my arms...

808
01:19:13,955 --> 01:19:16,858
...without copping a feel.

809
01:19:21,362 --> 01:19:25,200
Well...maybe one.

810
01:19:32,073 --> 01:19:36,978
-What?
-Well, I'm relieved.

811
01:19:39,013 --> 01:19:41,115
I mean, for a second l--

812
01:19:42,183 --> 01:19:45,553
I thought maybe you
thought last night was....

813
01:19:46,921 --> 01:19:48,690
Or that you would...

814
01:19:49,691 --> 01:19:51,192
...think....

815
01:19:52,994 --> 01:19:56,831
That would've blown Dr. Charles
out of the water, huh?

816
01:19:58,233 --> 01:20:02,604
Temporarily, maybe. But you'd
show your spots eventually.

817
01:20:03,438 --> 01:20:04,973
My spots?

818
01:20:05,607 --> 01:20:10,445
Come on, Eddie. Men never fail to do
what's in their nature to do.

819
01:20:14,849 --> 01:20:17,385
And what is that, Jane?

820
01:20:18,786 --> 01:20:21,589
Disappoint you?
Abandon you?

821
01:20:25,593 --> 01:20:28,263
What's really behind these theories?

822
01:20:30,198 --> 01:20:31,833
What are you hiding?

823
01:20:32,901 --> 01:20:34,502
Nothing.

824
01:20:37,972 --> 01:20:40,108
What you see is what you get.

825
01:20:41,709 --> 01:20:43,211
Is it?

826
01:20:46,648 --> 01:20:50,752
This is not about my nature.
This is about yours.

827
01:21:06,768 --> 01:21:08,303
-Hello.
-Janie?

828
01:21:08,636 --> 01:21:12,640
-Stephen, can I call you back?
-Your sister's in the hospital.

829
01:21:12,907 --> 01:21:15,376
We lost the baby, kiddo.

830
01:21:23,685 --> 01:21:26,020
Hey, Janie.

831
01:21:39,601 --> 01:21:41,469
Did you see Stephen?

832
01:21:42,604 --> 01:21:46,040
-I saw him in the hallway--
-Getting ice.

833
01:21:48,476 --> 01:21:49,978
God love him.

834
01:21:50,979 --> 01:21:53,848
They break so easily, don't they?

835
01:22:02,223 --> 01:22:08,062
Last weekend, he woke up in a panic.
He said he had to shop for the baby.

836
01:22:08,496 --> 01:22:12,333
You know how anal he is,
I thought he'd come back with...

837
01:22:12,800 --> 01:22:16,371
...thermometers and baby blankets
and safety gates.

838
01:22:17,138 --> 01:22:21,576
But when he walked in the door,
all he had was a little tiny bag.

839
01:22:21,876 --> 01:22:23,811
Inside was this...

840
01:22:26,181 --> 01:22:29,017
...this perfect little baseball mitt.

841
01:22:38,426 --> 01:22:42,864
He got it in his head
that it was gonna be a boy.

842
01:22:43,097 --> 01:22:44,732
Jane.

843
01:22:54,108 --> 01:22:56,444
Okay, I've got ice.

844
01:22:56,711 --> 01:23:01,115
I've got blankets.
I've got magazines.

845
01:23:09,691 --> 01:23:11,426
Look at my wife.

846
01:23:15,563 --> 01:23:18,700
Have you ever seen anyone
more beautiful?

847
01:23:19,534 --> 01:23:21,769
You're nuts.

848
01:23:53,835 --> 01:23:55,937
Diane, it's Jane.

849
01:23:57,605 --> 01:23:59,941
I've found Dr. Charles.

850
01:24:05,847 --> 01:24:08,449
Everybody ready to have a good time?

851
01:24:09,984 --> 01:24:12,554
You'll have to do better than that.

852
01:24:14,289 --> 01:24:17,692
Let me explain how this show's
gonna work, okay?

853
01:24:18,760 --> 01:24:21,129
Ray, do we have her on the line?

854
01:24:21,863 --> 01:24:24,966
Two minutes.
Magazine's putting her through.

855
01:24:25,300 --> 01:24:26,901
Two minutes.

856
01:24:27,802 --> 01:24:29,938
Diane, two minutes.

857
01:24:30,271 --> 01:24:34,209
So Diane's gonna come out
for about a 15-minute segment.

858
01:24:34,475 --> 01:24:39,080
The first interview's by telephone.
Dr. Marie Charles.

859
01:24:50,792 --> 01:24:54,929
Again, are you absolutely,
100% sure you want to do this?

860
01:24:55,196 --> 01:24:56,965
I'm sure. I'm sorry.

861
01:24:57,198 --> 01:25:00,802
-I want to be sure you're not insane.
-Maybe I am.

862
01:25:01,536 --> 01:25:04,472
-Here she is, Ray.
-Dr. Charles.

863
01:25:11,145 --> 01:25:15,483
Welcome. I rarely have the honor
to host such a distinguished...

864
01:25:15,717 --> 01:25:17,519
...and extraordinary guest.

865
01:25:17,719 --> 01:25:22,056
Today, Doctor Marie Charles
speaks out for the first time...

866
01:25:22,357 --> 01:25:26,861
-...since the publication--
-Already 20,000 hits on the web site.

867
01:25:27,929 --> 01:25:31,966
-Holy cow.
-The reclusive doctor has agreed...

868
01:25:32,267 --> 01:25:34,502
...to an exclusive phone interview.

869
01:25:34,736 --> 01:25:39,240
And I consider it a rare gift
from someone whose work...

870
01:25:39,574 --> 01:25:43,945
...has meant a tremendous amount
in my life, as I'm sure yours.

871
01:25:45,380 --> 01:25:47,348
Dr. Marie Charles.

872
01:25:48,750 --> 01:25:51,719
Hello, Dr. Charles. Are you there?

873
01:25:52,086 --> 01:25:54,455
Hello, Dr. Charles, can you hear me?

874
01:25:55,590 --> 01:25:57,559
I'm not getting anything.

875
01:25:59,761 --> 01:26:04,098
-Where the hell is she?
-We have a technical difficulty.

876
01:26:04,399 --> 01:26:06,734
We'll get it worked out.

877
01:26:09,604 --> 01:26:14,042
-Patch it through on another line.
-We only have one dedicated line.

878
01:26:18,780 --> 01:26:24,152
-Take us to commercial.
-She's here. She wants to go on.

879
01:26:24,752 --> 01:26:27,422
Hold that, hold that.
She's here.

880
01:26:27,755 --> 01:26:33,561
It seems the reason we've been unable
to get through telephonically...

881
01:26:33,761 --> 01:26:39,367
...is because she's here, having
decided to do the interview in person.

882
01:26:39,634 --> 01:26:43,004
-Holy shit.
-Let's not waste any more time.

883
01:26:43,271 --> 01:26:45,139
Welcome Dr. Marie Charles!

884
01:26:49,310 --> 01:26:52,380
-A little makeup. Just a little.
-Stop! Stop!

885
01:26:52,647 --> 01:26:54,749
Show yourself, Dr. Charles.

886
01:26:57,785 --> 01:26:59,387
Wake up!

887
01:27:06,594 --> 01:27:08,730
What? Where's Dr. Charles?

888
01:27:11,666 --> 01:27:15,603
There's no Dr. Charles.
There never was.

889
01:27:19,174 --> 01:27:21,609
I invented her, Diane.

890
01:27:26,181 --> 01:27:29,851
I invented her because
I had something to say.

891
01:27:31,886 --> 01:27:33,988
And somehow I thought...

892
01:27:34,856 --> 01:27:40,995
...if it were coming from a 65-year-
old Ph.D., you'd see it the way I had.

893
01:27:41,229 --> 01:27:46,634
As a truth, as a legitimate,
scientific truth.

894
01:27:47,635 --> 01:27:53,508
But it isn't.
It's completely ridiculous.

895
01:27:56,544 --> 01:28:00,548
I lied to you all, and I lied
to myself because...

896
01:28:01,482 --> 01:28:03,318
...the real truth is...

897
01:28:07,388 --> 01:28:10,725
...that I was heartbroken and lost.

898
01:28:11,559 --> 01:28:14,562
And I just wanted
to understand it somehow.

899
01:28:14,863 --> 01:28:19,234
I wanted it to be about them.

900
01:28:19,667 --> 01:28:23,705
So everything I thought I had figured
out was completely upside-down.

901
01:28:23,938 --> 01:28:28,176
I thought that this bull had gone to a
New Cow, but she was an Old Cow.

902
01:28:28,776 --> 01:28:34,182
What was I talking about?
I was comparing men to animals.

903
01:28:35,083 --> 01:28:38,419
Which, let's face it,
sometimes they are.

904
01:28:40,922 --> 01:28:43,091
But sometimes they are not.

905
01:28:43,958 --> 01:28:49,998
Sometimes you open the barn door,
or the hospital room door...

906
01:28:50,565 --> 01:28:52,534
...or the bedroom door...

907
01:28:55,303 --> 01:29:00,241
...and you find the real thing.
You find a guy who...

908
01:29:02,210 --> 01:29:06,648
...sits with you when you're at
your worst, knee-deep in Kleenex...

909
01:29:06,881 --> 01:29:12,320
...and your face looks like
a punching bag and you're a mess...

910
01:29:14,622 --> 01:29:17,759
...and he can still look at you
and tell you...

911
01:29:18,059 --> 01:29:22,897
...that Ray is not the last man
you're ever going to love.

912
01:29:38,313 --> 01:29:39,914
Eddie.

913
01:29:47,922 --> 01:29:50,291
Jane, you all right?

914
01:30:15,450 --> 01:30:16,951
Eddie!

915
01:30:18,553 --> 01:30:20,088
Eddie!

916
01:30:37,205 --> 01:30:41,276
Eddie! Eddie!
Stop! Stop!

917
01:30:54,822 --> 01:30:57,225
So, what you see is what you get?

918
01:30:59,561 --> 01:31:03,031
Minus a few gray hairs
and a Ph.D., yeah.

919
01:31:06,734 --> 01:31:09,404
I'm really sorry, Eddie.

920
01:31:12,106 --> 01:31:17,378
-You should have told me.
-I should've told you a lot of things.

921
01:31:18,379 --> 01:31:19,914
You were right.

922
01:31:21,516 --> 01:31:23,484
It was about my nature.

923
01:31:25,520 --> 01:31:30,792
Of everything you said to me
that night, what scared me most...

924
01:31:32,927 --> 01:31:35,597
...is that I would find it again.

925
01:31:36,931 --> 01:31:38,600
Because I have.

926
01:31:45,106 --> 01:31:47,542
Would you please say something?

927
01:31:51,980 --> 01:31:53,515
No.

928
01:32:15,336 --> 01:32:17,739
So you're saying....

929
01:32:19,607 --> 01:32:21,743
What have we got to lose?

930
01:32:22,510 --> 01:32:27,081
-Everything?
-Exactly.

